# ONL329 Export Error: Receipt Image Exceeded Accounting System Size Limit

If you see the error:

**“ONL329 Export Error: Error downloading receipt image — the file exceeded your accounting system’s size limit. The report exported without the PDF attachment.”**

this means the PDF attachments associated with the report were too large to be uploaded to QuickBooks Online.

The report itself still exports successfully, but the receipt PDFs are not included.

---

## Why ONL329 Happens

QuickBooks Online has file size limits for attachments.

If a receipt PDF exceeds QuickBooks’ size threshold, the system blocks the attachment upload during export. Expensify completes the report export but excludes the oversized PDF.

This is a QuickBooks Online file size limitation — not a report failure.

---

## What Happens When ONL329 Occurs

- The report exports successfully to QuickBooks Online.
- The PDF attachments are not included.
- The full report and all receipt images remain available in Expensify.

You can always cross-reference the report in Expensify to review the complete receipt details.

---

## How to Review Receipts After ONL329

Since the report remains available in Expensify:

1. Open the report in Expensify.
2. Click into the individual expenses.
3. View or download the receipt attachments as needed.

If your accounting team requires smaller attachments in QuickBooks Online, consider reducing the file size of the receipt before export.

---

# FAQ

## Does ONL329 mean the export failed?

No. The report exports successfully. Only the PDF attachment fails to upload.

---

## Were my receipts deleted?

No. All receipts remain stored in Expensify.

---

## Can I re-export the report with attachments?

If the PDF exceeds QuickBooks Online’s size limit, re-exporting will result in the same error unless the file size is reduced.

---

## Is ONL329 caused by Expensify settings?

No. ONL329 is caused by QuickBooks Online’s attachment size limit, not by Workspace settings in Expensify.
